<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Accused of Attempting to Setting Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 9 (Xinhua) -- General Omar Hajji Masalleh,
chairman of the Somali National Front, Friday accused Ethiopia of
attempting to establish an administration for the Somalis inside
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to journalists in south Mogadishu, General Masalleh
also accused Ethiopia of destabilizing Gedo region and creating
confusion among his faction and the Somali people as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the border town of Bulo Hawo indicate that the
Ethiopian forces stationed in the town are further tightening
their grip on the town and its surrounding areas.
</P>
<P>
After successfully restoring normalcy to the town, the
Ethiopian forces rounded up more than 20 people Thursday night.
Among the apprehended are General Abdulaziz All Barre, former
commander of the 26th Division of Somalia's former national army
and Hassan Abdi Hirey, former district commissioner of Dolow town
in Gedo region.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian forces have also arrested more than 16 gunmen and
 confiscated their guns.
</P>
<P>
According to some traditional leaders of Bulo Hawo town
contacted on the VHF radio Friday, the Ethiopian forces have
sealed off the town from every corner, even its border with Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The elders added that the Kenyan police have also closed their
border by deploying armed units so as to block the influx of
people moving to Kenya for security reasons.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopians have no rights to cross into Somalia and
apprehend people in their own country, General Masalleh said,
demanding the immediate and unconditional release of the
apprehended people and the withdrawal of the Ethiopian forces from
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Ethiopian forces Friday reportedly nominated
their own administration for the town. Mohamed Sheikh Ali Burale
has been nominated as the chairman of the town, while Nur Matan
and Abukar Sankus were made his deputies.
</P>
<P>
No immediate comment was available from the Ethiopian side.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
