<HEADLINE> U.N. Expects Turkey to Provide Humanitarian Aid to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees
(UNHCR) said here on Friday that it is waiting for the demand of
Turkish officials to contribute to the aid campaign for the
Kosovar refugees who took shelter in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Anatolia News Agency quoted UNHCR spokesman in Turkey Metin
Corabatir as saying that the U.N. is very grateful to Turkey since
it acts very generously and rapidly for the Kosovar refugees.
</P>
<P>
Over 8,000 Kosovar refugees have arrived in Turkey since the
air strikes launched by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
against Yugoslavia on March 24.
</P>
<P>
Corabatir pointed out that the U.N. is waiting for the demand
of Turkey to provide aid for the refugees staying in
northwestern Kirklareli province.
</P>
<P>
The delay in the demand of Turkey can affect the contribution
of the international community for the refugees in Turkey, said
the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Corabatir stressed that the U.N. can only provide more money to
this fund when Turkey officially demands aid from the U.N..
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
