<HEADLINE> UN Chief Weapons Inspector Barred From Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 9 (Xinhua) -- U.N. chief weapons
inspector Richard Butler was barred from attending Security
Council's consultations on Iraq, a U.N. diplomat said here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The diplomat said Russia had vowed to block Butler, Executive
Chairman of the United Nations Special Commission in charge of
dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass destruction, from ever
appearing before the Security Council in its closed session.
</P>
<P>
Butler, who had excluded from Council's Wednesday
consultations, decided to send his deputy, American Charles
Duelfer, in his place to attend the meeting this morning,
according to the diplomat.
</P>
<P>
Russia wants Butler dismissed and UNSCOM replaced by another
commission. Russia slammed his December report, which said Iraq
failed to cooperate fully with the U.N. arms inspectors.
</P>
<P>
Russia also blamed Butler for providing pretext for the United
States and Britain to launch military strikes against Iraq last
December by report that Iraq had not fully cooperated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
