<HEADLINE> Rios Beasts Kuerten to Enter Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- No. 2 seed Marcelo Rios beat No. 5
Gustavo Kuerten 6-4, 6-3 Friday to enter the semifinals of the
Estoril Open in Oeiras of Portuigal.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean, fighting back to form after a four-month layoff
with a back injury, targeted Kuerten's weaker backhand while the
Brazilian, who displayed occasional flashes of brilliance but
lacked consistency, sought to pin Rios on the backline.
</P>
<P>
The two clay-court specialists broke each other's serve early
in the first set before Rios, ranked 13th in the world, began to
get the upper hand.
</P>
<P>
In a clash between Spaniards, the 1996 Estoril titlist, No. 4
Albert Costa, overcame sixth-seeded Felix Mantilla 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
In another men's quarterfinal match, Frenchman Jerome Golmard
defeated Karim Alami of Morocco 6-4, 7-6 (7-1).
</P>
<P>
Costa and Golmard will meet in Saturday's semifinals.
</P>
<P>
No. 2 seed Todd Martin of the United States was due to meet
Brazilian Fernando Meligeni later in the day.
</P>
<P>
Men's top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov bowed out in the first round.
</P>
<P>
In the women's draw, unseeded Hungarian Rita Kuti Kis, who
eliminated top seed Anke Huber, continued her charge with a 6-3, 6-
0 victory over Anca Barna of Germany. 
</P>
