<HEADLINE> Car Sales in Britain March Ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON April 9 (Xinhua) - Commercial vehicle registrations
soared this march by 27.5 percent, from 30902 in 1998 to 39409,
according to the latest figures by the Society of Motor
Manufacturers and Traders(SMMT).
</P>
<P>
The introduction of 'T' registration vehicles from 1 March
particularly affected smaller sectors of the market. LCVs under
1800kg are up 24.4 percent; those from 1801-3500kg soared by 32.6
percent; and light 4x4 utilities rose 27.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The heavier end was less affected, due mainly to pre-planned
buying cycles and the repercussions of pre-budget VED uncertainty,
said the SMMT.
</P>
<P>
However, the trucks sector did enlarge by 17.9 percent to 5632
from 4777 last year. Buses and coaches were similarly buoyant,
enjoying a healthy swell from 448 to 545.
</P>
<P>
Year to date (YTD), the overall market for the first quarter is
slightly down on 1998's strong performance, down 5.2 percent with
72553 registrations compared to last year's 76573. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
