<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Needs Popular Science Policy: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe needs a science and
technology policy document which represents the aspirations of its
people, Higher Education and Technology Minister Ignatius Chombo
said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the official opening of a seminar on science and technology
dialog for policy makers, Chombo said that his ministry would
provide money to the policy makers to draft the policy document.
</P>
<P>
"It has become obvious that countries which are going to
benefit from the process of globalization are those which have
made past investments in science and technology," said the
minister.
</P>
<P>
A survey would reveal that most of the products being sold were
imported, he said, adding that Zimbabwe had to make progress in
the field of technology.
</P>
<P>
Participants noted that it is necessary to set up a science and
 technology data bank and to improve the communication between
researchers and scientists.
</P>
<P>
The one-day seminar was attended by representatives from
researchers, scientists, policy makers and the private sector.
</P>
