<HEADLINE> New Technologies to Improve Business Environmental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON April 9 (Xinhua) - New technologies to help businesses
reduce their impact on the environment will get a helping hand
from the Government in a new scheme announced Friday by Energy
Minister John Battle.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to local entrepreneurs at a conference in Cambridge,
Battle said the Sustainable Technologies Initiative (STI) will
help UK businesses face up to the challenges of sustainable
development.
</P>
<P>
Over the next three years, 7.8 million pounds will be available
to support the development of new technologies that will help
business by:
</P>
<P>
- being more efficient in the use of resources;
</P>
<P>
- producing less waste and pollution;
</P>
<P>
- aiming for greater social equity in their operations and
products.
</P>
<P>
Proposed programs under the STI will cover the development of
more sustainable manufacturing processes and more sustainable
products.
</P>
<P>
Battle said sustainable technologies could not only reduce the
impact of business on the environment and society, but also
improve their competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
However, "sustainability will be one of the major challenges
facing business as we go into the next century. To meet this
challenge we will need to develop new processes, new products, and
new ways of doing business," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
