<HEADLINE> China Urges Parties Concerned to Show Political </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China Friday called on
parties concerned to show political will in solving the issue of
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the press after attending Security Council
consultations on Iraq, Chinese Deputy Permanent Representative to
the United Nations Shen Guofang said the Security Council had
started the process of reviewing the Iraqi panels' report.
</P>
<P>
Shen said there were some constructive proposals in the reports
and he hoped that the reports would serve as a basis for the
Council to find a way out of the current deadlock regarding Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Shen said the solution to the current deadlock hinged upon the
political will of the parties concerned, and moreover, cooperation
from Iraq was also very important.
</P>
<P>
Shen said China supported U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan in
continuing to play an active role in the current process.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that the continued airstrikes in the so-called no-fly
zones in Iraq were not conducive, he urged the parties concerned
to stop the military operations as soon as possible so as to
create a good atmosphere for an early solution of the Iraq
question. 
</P>
