<DOCNO> XIE19990410.0042 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan Director-Designate to Anti-graft Body Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Aaron Ringera, the newly-appointed
director of the Kenya Anti-Corruption Authority (KACA), is back to
head the authority following a court decision to quash an earlier
order stopping him from acting on behalf of the authority.
</P>
<P>
Justice Richard Kuloba restored Ringera to lead the
organization, saying its former boss John Harun Mwau, who had
obtained the order earlier, did not demonstrate the loss he would
suffer if Ringera was allowed to continue in office pending
determination of the suit.
</P>
<P>
"Concerning what has already been done in the fight against
corruption, it is not fair to suspend the operations," Kuloba
said. "If the suspension is upheld, the current holder of the
position will continue suffering embarrassment."
</P>
<P>
Kenya's High Court Thursday suspended the operations of the
entire Kenya Anti-Corruption Authority following an application
filed by Mwau, the immediate former director.
</P>
<P>
Ringera was named as the head of KACA on March 23 by Kenyan
President Daniel arap Moi. The appointment was seen as a step
forward in the way to the resumption of aid talks with the
International Monetary Fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
