<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Opposition MP Arrested Over Murder Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A law-maker of the main opposition
Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) was arrested here on Saturday
on charges of involvement in killing two ruling party leaders
recently.
</P>
<P>
Alamgir Kabir, elected in 1996 from Noagaon constituency,
northwest Bangladesh, was arrested by police at Monipuripara, east
of the Parliament Complex, the official BSS news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"We have arrested the member of parliament on the basis of
specific charges obtaining permission from the appropriate
authority," a senior official of the Dhaka Metropolitan Police was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
But Kabir denied the charges and said he was "falsely
implicated" in the murder case, in which two leaders of the ruling
Awami League's local unit were gunned down in Noagaon district on
March 31.
</P>
<P>
BNP Secretary General Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan condemned the arrest
and demanded the immediate release of Kabir, sources said.
</P>
</TEXT>
