<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Launch Rural Internet Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will launch a "Community
Internet Project" soon to explore contributions of the information
super highway in the field of mass communication in rural areas,
the official BSS news agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The project would be launched "as a pilot project" in three
learning centers in Sylhet and a supported center in Narsingdi,
two districts in northeast Bangladesh, Additional Chief Engineer
of Local Government Engineering Department (LGED) Mohammad
Shahidul Hassan was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The project is aimed at evaluating the Internet's application
in mass communication and education delivery systems in the rural
areas, he said.
</P>
<P>
A memorandum of understanding has been signed between the LGED
and some companies and organizations, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Internet is still something new to the majority of the
126-million population of Bangladesh, where the adult literacy
rate is 51.2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
