<HEADLINE> Roundup: Building A Better World (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIANDU (Zhejiang), April 10 (Xinhua) -- Volunteers
participating in the 10-day workcamp in Xiandu, east China's
Zhejiang Province, reluctantly expressed fond farewells today.
</P>
<P>
The volunteers from a number of countries, including China,
Japan, the Netherlands and Australia, focused on environmental
protection and expanding cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The group planted trees, repaired roads and provided various
volunteer services to residents in Xiandu, in addition to visit
cultural relics in the local area.
</P>
<P>
"The volunteers planted the seeds of friendship in China," said
Scottish volunteer Gavin Starks. "I'll return to the lovely town
of Xiandu someday," he added.
</P>
<P>
The beautiful scenery in Xiandu left volunteers with a deep
impression. Kayano Takashi, an elderly Japanese man participating
in the China International Young Volunteers Workcamp, said that
everyone should make an effort to protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
Joo Young-oh, a teenager from the Republic of Korea, said that
environmental protection is a global issue. He added that mankind
should coexist with the nature and leave a harmonious world for
later generations.
</P>
<P>
Australian Graeme Smith, who currently studies environmental
impact assessment at Beijing University, said he plans to
interview Chinese environmental experts and representatives from
nongovernmental Chinese organizations.
</P>
<P>
"I also plan to study the relationship between NGOs in China,
as well as environmental protection organizations and the nation's
policies concerning related issues."
</P>
<P>
The successful experiences gained in Xiandu have provided him
with good material for later environmental protection efforts,
according to Smith.
</P>
<P>
Starks expressed hope that the work of the volunteers will
provide Chinese people with a greater awareness of the fact that
China should avoid Western mistakes regarding the issue and in
turn enable them to enjoy a better environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
