<HEADLINE> Iran Determined to Support Palestinians: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi stated Saturday that Iran is still determined to support
the ideals of Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting head of the Political Department of
the Palestine Liberation Organization Farouk Kadoumy, Kharrazi
said despite foreign pressure, Tehran stands to support the causes
of the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
The issue of Jerusalem is not a Palestinian problem, but a
problem of the world of Islam, the Islamic Republic News Agency
quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the importance for a continued Palestinian
resistance to the Israeli expansionist policies, saying that most
of the crises gripping the region have their roots in Israel's
expansionist policies.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Iran's disapproval of the Middle East peace
talks, saying that Iran had predicted the futility of the talks.
</P>
<P>
Iran, which has been calling for military struggle against
Israel, strongly criticized Palestinian leaders for making
compromise with the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
Kadoumi, who arrived here Friday, praised Iran's stands
toward the Palestinian cause, saying "from the very beginning, we
were of the belief that the Oslo agreement would not lead to a
just peace" to the region.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. failure to remain impartial and the increasing
expansionist policies of the Israeli regime have contributed to
further violation of Palestinian rights, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
