<HEADLINE> Plenary Meeting of MSAR Preparatory Committee Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese vice-Premier Qian Qichen
today expressed his confidence that the Selection Committee for
the First Government of the Macao Special Administrative Region (
MSAR) will be fully capable of selecting a candidate for the
position as the region's first chief executive.
</P>
<P>
The 200-odd member Selection Committee was announced today at
the closing session of 7th Plenary Meeting of the Preparatory
Committee for the MSAR.
</P>
<P>
Qian, chairman of the Preparatory Committee, said that
formation of the Selection Committee is the core of ending
colonial rule over Macao and establishing the MSAR.
</P>
<P>
Members, all influential figures in Macao, have participated in
various aspects of social and public affairs, according to Qian.
</P>
<P>
He said the fact that Portuguese descendants with permanent
Macao residence have been elected to the Selection Committee
demonstrates the broad representation on the body.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting ended with the adoption of three documents
covering methods for forming the first MSAR Legislative Council,
the decision on establishing an independent committee responsible
of recommending judges and the decision on the emblem, seal and
flag of public institutions of the MSAR.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that the important documents will form a solid
foundation for the establishment of the MSAR.
</P>
<P>
The methods for forming the first Legislative Council mainly
involves the establishment of the Legislative Council in terms of
both principle and procedure.
</P>
<P>
The Selection Committee will also be responsible of selecting
new members of the Legislative Council once there are vacancies,
said Qian.
</P>
<P>
He noted the formation of an independent committee to recommend
judges is part of preparations for establishing the MSAR judiciary.
</P>
<P>
Judges for Macao courts at various levels were for many years
appointed by the Portuguese government. However, local judicial
officers have been appointed in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Formation of the MSAR judiciary is one of the Preparatory
Committee's important tasks in accordance with the 1993 decision
of the National People's Congress, said Qian, adding that the
committee will also formulate stipulations governing the formation
of various other MSAR judicial departments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
