<HEADLINE> Canada Scraps Airlift After Refugees Reject Offer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Canada announced Friday that it
will cancel plans to fly 5,000 Kosovo refugees to Canada because
most of them insisted on staying as close as possible to their
Kosovo homeland.
</P>
<P>
The airlift was originally set to begin Monday at the earliest.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Immigration Minister Lucienne Robillard said the
decision to cancel the airlift was made at the request of Sadako
Ogata, United Nations High Commissioner (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
"(Ogata) said the majority of people should remain in the
region to permit repatriation with security when the situation
allows," said Robillard.
</P>
<P>
The UNHCR has reported that just under 517,000 people had left
Kosovo since NATO's bombing of Yugoslavia started on March 24.
</P>
