<HEADLINE> Hangzhou to Rebuild West Lake Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Hangzhou, capital of east
China's Zhejiang Province known for its picturesque scenery, plans
to rebuild a bridge on famous West Lake.
</P>
<P>
The 200-meter by 3-meter bridge, demolished in 1932 due to
deteriorating conditions, will be rebuilt as a pedestrian crossing,
according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Traditional styles and modern technique will be used to rebuild
the structure in an effort to restore the historical significance
and maintain the harmonious ambiance of the lake, they said.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government is currently soliciting designs for
the bridge and will announce a final decision after consulting
experts and citizens.
</P>
<P>
The new bridge will link two scenic sites in the West Lake
resort area and will provide visitors will an excellent view of
lotus growing in the lake.
</P>
<P>
Construction will commence in June and is scheduled for
completion by October 1, China's National Day.  
</P>
