<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Threatens to Hit Backers of S. Leone Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The West African Peace-keeping
force of ECOMG has threatened to bomb all channels involved in
the supply of heavy arms to the rebels of the Revolutionary
United Front (RUF) in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG force commander Major General Felix Mujakpero said in
capital Freetown Friday that the present tension between ECOMOG
and the Liberian government was sparked off by a massive arms
shipment by Liberia on behalf of the rebels in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
"We shall proceed to strike at all the channels involved in
the movement of heavy arms and ammunition to the rebels by land,
sea and air, " The Post Express paper Saturday quoted the
commander as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, a Ukrainian registered cargo
aircraft ANTENOV 124 carrying 68 tons of arms arrived in
Ouagaduogou, capital of Burkina Faso, and was parked at the
presidential wing of the airport.
</P>
<P>
The arms were transported to Robertuille International Airport
in Monrovia and subsequently to Gbanga, a neighboring town in
Liberia with Sierra Leone for onward delivery to the RUF rebels,
it added.
</P>
<P>
Mujakperuo specifically warned the government of President
Charles Tayor that "we will no longer watch this mischief by
supposed leaders continuing side by side with the peace efforts
by the government of Sierra Leone."
</P>
<P>
He cautioned that the encouragement being given by the leaders
of Liberia and Burkina Faso toward the continuation of the war in
Sierra Leone by the rebels must be condemned.
</P>
<P>
The ECOMOG commander warned that ECOMOG will not hesitate to
strike where necessary to forestall all the schemes being
packaged to undermine the peace efforts in the sub-region.
</P>
</TEXT>
