<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Tourism Sector Attracts Investors (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A Japanese airline recently opened
a new route to Xi'an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi
Province, home of the "Terra Cotta Warriors".
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 100,000 Japanese tourists with strong
curiosity and great interest in ancient Chinese culture visit the
city on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The new route will provide greater opportunities for more
Japanese to learn about the historic city, according to a local
tourism official.
</P>
<P>
Emperors from 13 Chinese dynasties established ancient capitals
in the province which is located in the middle reaches of the
Yellow River, the so-called cradle of the 5,000-year-old Chinese
Civilization.
</P>
<P>
The province hosted a record 600,000 foreign tourists and more
than 25 million domestic visitors in 1998, up eight percent on the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also reveal that Shaanxi has hosted an average 20
million domestic and 500,000 foreign tourists over the past five
years. Tourism has grown into one of the province's pillar
industries and has attracted increasing attention from foreign
investors.
</P>
