biggest tourism project with a major local exhibition company.
They plan to invest 200 million U.S. dollars to build a large
garden and palace complex based on the ancient architectural style
in Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
The structures will feature architectural styles dating to four
flourishing ancient Chinese dynasties -- Zhou (771-221 B.C.), Qin
(221-207 B.C.), Han (206 B.C.-220) and Tang (618-907).
