<HEADLINE> Macao Banks to Cut Deposit Rate Next Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Association of Banks has
announced that local deposit rate will be lowered by 0.25 percent
beginning from next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made Friday right following a fresh rate
cut in Hong Kong, as Macao's currency of pataca is pegged on Hong
Kong dollar.
</P>
<P>
Readjusted deposit rate in Macao will be 3.5 percent per annum,
and the rate for deposits which can only be drawn with a notice
made seven days in advance will be 4.25 percent per annum.
</P>
<P>
It will be the seventh interest rate cut in Macao since January
1998, and the new rate will be the lowest since February 1997.
</P>
<P>
Banking sources said that the cut will help ease financial
pressure in manufacturing and real estate sectors to some extent,
but it is not enough to stimulate the overall economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
