<HEADLINE> Macao Examinees Tested for Study at Inland Universities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Two-day entrance exams were
launched at the Macao University on Saturday for universities in
the inland areas of China to enroll Macao students striving for
master's degrees and doctorates.
</P>
<P>
It is the sixth time that the Macao Foundation collaborates
with China's Ministry of Education to manage such an annual
examination in Macao.
</P>
<P>
A total of 388 people in Macao applied for the examination, and
380 of whom turned out to be qualified examinees vying for 27
universities in China's inland areas, according to Delina Io, a
staff member of the foundation.
</P>
<P>
"The examinees come from various trades in Macao, and a large
number of them are government employees, teachers and those
working in service trades," Delina said, adding that there of
course are some this year's graduates.
</P>
<P>
"The cooperation between the Macao Foundation and the Ministry
of Education has helped train hosts of professionals for Macao's
economic and social development," she said.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, the foundation initiated a scholarship aimed at
encouraging Macao people to struggle for master's degrees or
doctorates in Macao, China's inland areas and other overseas
places.More than 30 people win the scholarship each years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Gang, an official with the Ministry of Education, came to
Macao to help manage the tests. "Macao people have a high
enthusiasm for studying in universities in the inland areas, which
indicates that Macao people approve the educational level of in
the inland areas."
</P>
<P>
Almost all of those who completed their studies have returned
to work in Macao. "Thy show full confidence in Macao's future as
Macao is returning to the motherland," Jiang Gang said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education is working on a network project based
on Internet. As soon as the network is set up, applicants can make
convenient and fast contacts with the universities they want to
enter,according to Jiang Gang.  
</P>
