<HEADLINE> Chongqing Enjoys Rapid First Quarter Industrial Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Chongqing
Municipality reported substantial industrial growth in the first
quarter this year.
</P>
<P>
The municipality's industrial value added for the first three
months of the year surged 14.9 percent on an annual basis to 5.2
billion yuan, according to the municipal government.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed the rapid growth to government policies
designed to increase investments and expand domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that the municipality's fixed asset
investments hit 10.3 billion yuan last year, up 17.4 percent on an
annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Increased investments have fueled the production of raw
materials and basic industrial products, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Chongqing's sales-production ratio has grown
remarkably in the wake of a booming market. For example, the sales/
production ratio for both textiles and chemical products grew by
21 percentage points, with the ratio for electronic products and
light industrial products rising by 10 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The sales volume for motor vehicles and other products
manufactured by national defense industries, which account for
nearly 25 percent of Chongqing's total industrial sales value,
increased by 37.7 percent to 4.51 billion yuan in the three-month
period and effectively reversed last year's loss-making conditions.
</P>
</TEXT>
