<HEADLINE> Selection Committee for First Macao SAR Government Formed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The two hundred member-committee
responsible for selecting the first government of the Macao
Special Administrative Region (MSAR) were formed today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Selection Committee, composed entirely of permanent Macao
residents, will be responsible of selecting candidates for the
MSAR's chief executive within 45 days.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen expressed the hope that committee
members will earnestly fulfill their duties under the principle of
impartiality, justice, openness, democracy and honesty.
</P>
<P>
Some 185 committee members from all walks of life were elected
by secret ballot during the 7th Plenary Meeting of the Preparatory
Committee for the MSAR which closed today.
</P>
<P>
Four Macao deputies to the National People's Congress (NPC)
automatically became members of the Selection Committee in
accordance a relevant NPC decision.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 11 members, Macao members of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), were selected by CPPCC members.
</P>
<P>
The first plenary meeting of the Selection Committee will be
held in Macao on April 23 to nominate candidates of the first
chief executive, according to a decision reached during a meeting
of the chairman and vice-chairmen of the Preparatory Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
