<HEADLINE> Israeli Navy Fire at Palestinian Fishing Boat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- One Israeli naval vessel opened fire
at a Palestinian fishing boat off the southern coast of the Gaza
Strip Saturday, wounding two Palestinian fishermen.
</P>
<P>
The wounded Palestinian fishermen were taken to Khan Yunis
Hospital for treatment and one of them was in a very serious
condition, according to a Palestinian official.
</P>
<P>
Israeli military said that the incident occurred Saturday
morning at the Mediterranean Sea, some 25 kilometers off the
southern coast of the Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli naval patrol vessel intercepted the Palestinian
fishing boasts and asked them to stop for inspection, but one of
the fishing boats did not stop and tried to flee, so the patrol
vessel opened fire at it while in chasing, the military said.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the Palestinian National Authority are at dispute
over fishing areas off the coast of the Gaza Strip. Israel insists
that the Palestinians can only fish at a distance of 12 kilometers
from the coast, while the Palestinian side said it should be 20
kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
