<HEADLINE> Singapore Deputy PM to Visit US Technopreneurial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Deputy Prime Minister
Tony Tan Keng Yam will lead a mission to visit U.S.
technopreneurial nodes from April 12 to 24, as part of the
country's efforts to build a critical mass of technopreneurial
talent.
</P>
<P>
The National Science and Technology Board (NSTB) said in a
press release that the 12-day visit will take Tony Tan's team to
New York; the Research Triangle Park, North Carolina; Boston,
Massachusetts; Austin, Texas and the Silicon Valley.
</P>
<P>
With an aim to acquaint themselves with and get a better
understanding of U.S. efforts in promoting and developing
technopreneurship, the team will meet technopreneurs, venture
capitalists, investment bankers and academia to get their feedback
on Singapore's technopreneurship strategy, the NSTB said.
</P>
<P>
Tony Tan announced at a press conference Thursday that
Singapore will launch a systematic, comprehensive strategic plan
to develop and attract technopreneurship talent to Singapore
through four initiatives centering on education, facilities,
regulations and financing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
