<HEADLINE> Chechen President Escapes Another Assassination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Aslan Maskhadov, president of
Russia's Chechen Republic, escaped another assassination attempt
on Saturday, the second in three weeks, a Chechen official said.
</P>
<P>
Chechen security forces defused a bomb discovered along the way
that Maskhadov was to drive to a gathering of supporters at Stary
Atagi, a village south of the Chechen capital, Grozny. The
president later made the trip safely, said the official from the
Chechen Security Ministry.
</P>
<P>
On March 21, Maskhadov narrowly escaped assassination when a
bomb exploded near his motorcade in Grozny.
</P>
<P>
Maskhadov, who used to be the leader of the Chechen separatists
during the 1994-96 war with the Russian Federation in Chechnya,
became the president of the republic in February 1997. 
