<HEADLINE> Pak Speaker Calls China Major Player on World Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China has emerged as a major
player on the international political scene and is playing a
stabilizing role for regional and global peace and security.
</P>
<P>
"The policies pursued by China have a special significance for
the developing world," Ellahi Bukhsh Soomro, speaker of Pakistan's
National Assembly, said here Saturday in his introductory remarks
before a speech delivered by his visiting Chinese counterpart, Li
Peng.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident that China will continue to strengthen its
cooperation with the developing countries to promote their
legitimate rights and interests," he added.
</P>
<P>
At the turn of the new millennium, the entire world's focus is
on China as "it promises to emerge as a trading giant, an economic
 powerhouse and takes its legitimate place among the most
important leaders in the comity of nations," Soomro said, adding,
"This is China's destiny."
</P>
<P>
Praising the policies pursued by China, he said, "they are
founded on the immutable principles of peaceful coexistence and
mutuality of benefit."
</P>
<P>
"China has always firmly opposed the unjust use of force or
threat of use of force and stands for the peaceful settlement of
all disputes and conflicts," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan applauds China's constant opposition to regional and
global hegemonism," Soomro said, adding that "China's role in
promoting a just, fair and equitable world economic and political
order has won her universal respect and admiration."
</P>
<P>
On the Pak-China bilateral relations, the speaker said the
relations between the two friendly neighbors stand out as a model
of inter-state conduct and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"The relations have withstood the test of time and remain
strong and vibrant in the face of multiple challenges and
pressures," Soomro added.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and China, he said, have always stood by and supported
 each other and the two countries would continue to do so in the
coming years, said Soomro.
</P>
<P>
"Indeed China occupies the pride of place in our foreign policy
 priorities and objectives. Mutual trust and confidence are the
building blocks of this edifice," the speaker said.
</P>
<P>
Soomro spoke highly of the significant contributions made by
Li, who was elected as chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress of China in March 1998, to shaping
China's enlightened domestic and international policies.
</P>
<P>
Li, who served as China's premier for a whole decade from 1988
to 1998, had also made great contributions to China's outstanding
 economic growth and development, Soomro noted.
</P>
<P>
The speaker described Li as "a trusted friend of Pakistan held
in high esteem by us." "His personal contribution to further
enhancing bilateral relations between Pakistan and China is deeply
etched in the chronicles of the history of our age-old ties." he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
