<HEADLINE> East-West China Cooperation Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A total of 258 cooperation
contracts and agreements involving the use of 3.3 billion US
dollar overseas funds were signed at the '99 China East-West
Cooperation and Investment Trade Fair, which ended today in this
capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day fair, 204 contracts for 1,300 items of high-
tech development and patent transactions were signed with a total
trade value of 1.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The 23 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions
attending the fair also made 414 inter-provincial cooperation
project contracts with combined investment of 8.83 billion yuan
and 290 cooperative agreements with a total investment of 9.73
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
This year's fair, co-sponsored by the State Economic and Trade
Commission and the State Administration of Internal Trade as well
as the provincial governments of Jiangsu, Anhui, Sichuan, Shaanxi
and municipalities of Beijing, Shanghai and Tianjin, attracted 29
trade delegations, 6,200 enterprises and 25,000 Chinese and
foreign businesspeople. 
