<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Farmers Urge End to Attacks on Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 10 (Xinhua)-- The Vietnam Farmers' Association
(VFA) has joined Vietnam's public opinion to demand an immediate
end to all military attacks against the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
According to a report of Vietnam News Agency on Saturday, said
in a recent statement that together with world public opinion for
peace and justice, the VFA strongly protests against the brutal
air raids launched by NATO and the United States since March 23
against Yugoslavia, an independent and sovereign nation.
</P>
<P>
As victims of war, the association said, the Vietnamese people
experienced numerous sufferings and losses and are still exerting
great efforts to overcome its consequences, especially that of
Agent Orange, a chemical toxicant used during the Vietnam War.
</P>
<P>
"We, therefore, demand that the military attack against
Yugoslavia be immediately stopped and that the Kosovo crisis be
settled through peaceful negotiations," the association said.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese Foreign Ministry, the Vietnam War Veterans'
Association, the Vietnam Journalists' Association and other
Vietnamese government departments and other organizations have
issued statements to protest against and demand an immediate end
to NATO air strikes on Yugoslavia and called for a peaceful
settlement of the Kosovo problem. 
</P>
