<DOCNO> XIE19990410.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Continue Consolidate Sino-Pak Ties: Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese leader Li Peng
 said here Saturday that China will continue to consolidate and
strengthen the good-neighborly friendship and mutually beneficial
cooperation with Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech here at the Convention Center organized by
Ellahi Bukhsh Soomro, speaker of Pakistan's National Assembly, Li
said that to continue to cement the Sino-Pak friendly and
cooperative ties is an important policy of China's.
</P>
<P>
This "not only serves the fundamental interests of our two
peoples, but also contributes to peace and stability in this
region and the world at large," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Li's speech covered the regional, international as well as
bilateral issues. He also briefed those present on China's
economic construction and its efforts to perfect its legislative
procedures.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Pak friendship is long-standing, thriving on a solid
foundation, said Li, who is chairman of the Standing Committee of
the National People's Congress (NPC) of China.
</P>
<P>
"Our two countries and peoples have been together through thick
and thin and shared weal and woe," Li said, adding that no matter
what happens on the international scene or in the respective
countries, the Sino-Pakistani relations have always been
developing steadily.
</P>
<P>
"The Sino-Pak friendly and cooperative relations built nearly
half a century ago have stood the test of time, displaying as it
does great vitality," Li noted.
</P>
<P>
He also said the relationship between China and Pakistan could
be called "an example of friendship and cooperation between
countries with different social systems."
</P>
<P>
Li described the exchanges and cooperation between the NPC and
Pakistan's National Assembly as fruitful. "Such friendly
interchanges have played a significant part in developing
Sino-Pak partnership of all-round cooperation," he added.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that there would be more contacts and
exchanges of legislative experience between people from all
circles, leaders of the legislative bodies, special committees,
friendship groups and law-makers from the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li said he was confident that with the unremitting efforts of
the two governments and peoples, the Sino-Pak partnership of
all-round cooperation oriented toward the 21st century would bear
even more fruits.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, in his introduction speech, Soomro praised the
traditional, time-honored Pakistan-China relations and China's
economic construction. He also expressed his appreciation of the
policies pursued by China in the international arena.
</P>
<P>
Present at the speech were some 500 people including members of
the Pakistani Senate and National Assembly, cabinet members and
foreign diplomatic envoys in Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
