<HEADLINE> China Dominate Women's Singles in Japan Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China dominate the women's singles
competitions as Gong Zhichao and Ye Zhaoying made the final an all-
Chinese affair at the Japan Open badminton tournament here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Gong Zhichao repeated her excellent
performance at the All England quarterfinals, beating the same
opponent Kim Ji-Hyun of South Korea 11-0, 11-6.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the other semifinal match, world champion Ye
Zhaoying beat a challenge from her young teammate Gong Ruina 11-5,
11-6.
</P>
<P>
Gong Zhichao said Ye Zhaoying would be a much tougher prospect
in the final. "When I beat her last year, I was very surprised,
but I've never beaten her in big events. It is very difficult to
beat her again because she is apparently a better player right now.
" Gong Zhichao said.
</P>
<P>
The men's singles final will feature world number one Peter
Gade Christensen of Denmark and Sun Jun of China.
</P>
<P>
Peter Gade Christensen beat Wong Choong Hann of Malaysia 15-8,
15-12 in the semifinal while Sun Jun defeated his compatriot Chen
Hong 15-9, 15-12.
</P>
<P>
Sun Jun, the Grand Prix Final winner, has beaten Gade
Christensen in their last two encounters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
