<HEADLINE> Six Drown in Boat Capsize in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Six secondary school
students drowned and six more are still missing when a passenger
boat capsized after colliding with another boat Friday evening on
in East Malaysia's Sarawak state, the Malaysian national news
agency Bernama reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
However, 43 others on the boat were saved by residents from the
nearby kampungs (villages), Bernama said quoting a police officer.
</P>
<P>
The boat, licensed to ferry 12 people, but with 55 people,
mainly students, on board collided into a boat carrying swan
timber in the Batang Saribas river near Pusa, 300 kilometers from
Kuching, Sarawak state's capital, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The boat's skipper, who was saved, has been detained to assist
police investigations into the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
