<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Arrives in New Delhi For Working Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Palestine President Yasser
Arafat arrived here Friday night for a one-day working visit
during which he will exchange views with the Indian leaders on
issues of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
Arafat is scheduled to meet Indian President Kocheril Raman
Narayanan and Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee on Saturday and
expected to seek support for his plan to declare an independent
Palestinian state later this year.
</P>
<P>
A brief press release issued last night by the Ministry of
External Affairs said that Arafat would discuss matters of mutual
interest including the Middle East peace process and the situation
in the region.
</P>
<P>
Before arriving here, Arafat said Friday in Dhaka, Bangladesh,
that he had visited many countries and was going to visit more to
hold consultations with world leaders on his plan to declare an
independent state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
