<HEADLINE> Guatemala Offers to Conditionally Assist Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The Guatemalan government said
Friday it could take some Kosovo refugees who fled war following
NATO air strikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Guatemalan Foreign Minister Eduardo Stein said his country
could only take the refugees temporarily since it was burdened
with regional immigrants.
</P>
<P>
Stein said he would call on the other Central American nations
to help shelter some of the Kosovo refugees.
</P>
<P>
He urged the Central American nations to build camps and
provide necessities of life for the refugees.
</P>
<P>
Stein added that the Kosovo refugees would be allowed to stay
in Guatemala till the conflict in Yugoslavia comes to an end.
</P>
</TEXT>
