<HEADLINE> Highlights of Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin held talks with visiting Qatar
Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Khalifa Al-Thani at the Great Hall of the
People in downtown Beijing Friday afternoon. Jiang noted that
harmonious international relations can only occur when every
country respects each other, seeks common ground while reserving
differences and co-exists peacefully with each other.
</P>
<P>
-- China and Qatar yesterday issued a joint press communique,
which said that the two countries have agreed to enter the 21st
century by establishing a solid and stable relationship.
</P>
<P>
-- No damage or aftershock has been reported after an
earthquake measuring 7.0 on the Richter Scale hit northeast
China's Jilin Province on Thursday night, local seismologists said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Visiting Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said Thursday in
Washington that both China and the United States should spare no
effort to further the Sino-U.S. relations for the fundamental
interests of the two peoples and for the sake of peace and
development of the world. Zhu made these remarks during talks with
U.S. President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
-- China and Pakistan Friday reiterated their resolve to
further develop the friendly relations and cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of China's National People's Congress
Standing Committee, the Chinese legislature, said Friday in
Islamabad during talks with Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
that it is China's consistent position to consolidate and fortify
the existing friendship with Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
-- The 7th Plenary Meeting of the Preparatory Committee for the
Macao Special Administrative Region (MSAR) opened Friday at the
Great Hall of the People in Beijing. Chinese Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen noted that electing the Selection Committee for the First
Government of the MSAR through secret ballot is an important task
of the plenary meeting.
</P>
<P>
China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- China and the United States have achieved significant
breakthroughs in negotiations to allow China into the World Trade
Organization (WTO), Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and U.S. President
Bill Clinton announced Thursday in Washington at a White House
press conference.
</P>
<P>
-- As China's accession to the WTO becomes an achievable goal
in a near future, the National People's Congress, China's
legislature, has stepped up legislation to get the country
prepared for WTO requirements. The NPC Friday announced the
drafting of the Government Procurement Law, which governs an
important part of the WTO package. 
</P>
