<HEADLINE> Sichuan Improves Tourist Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province has launched a
campaign to turn the area into a prime location for ecological and
cultural tours.
</P>
<P>
A tourism plan was drawn up for this southwest area at a cost
of five million yuan, paid for by the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, Chengdu, the provincial capital will be
transformed into a commercial, communications and tourism center
as well as a terminal for transferring tourists to other tourism
zones, including those in west Sichuan, Mount Leshan and Mount
Emei, and Zigong-Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
After giving top priority to road building local authorities
reckon that by 2005 all the tourism zones will be linked by
expressways.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan, with a population of nearly 100 million, is one of the
most scenic provinces in the country, featured by its lovely
mountains surrounding the Chengdu Plain as well as many historic
sites. 
</P>
</TEXT>
