During an interview with local TV, Majko voiced support to the
self-claimed government headed by Hasim Thaci.
</P>
<P>
Before Thaci's "government," established on April 2, there had
been another exile "government" of Kosovo ethnic Albanians with
Bujar Bukoshi as the "prime minister."
</P>
<P>
Saying it is high time to reconsider the status of Kosovo,
Majko added that the Rambouillet peace agreement reached in
February is still alive and open to discussions in this regard,
referring to granting independence to the province. 
