<HEADLINE> Drugs Hidden in Shoes Seized in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Colombian anti-drug
police seized two kilograms of heroine and 12 kilograms of cocaine
hidden in a small cargo of shoes.
</P>
<P>
The heroine was seized in the Cartagena resort, where police
intercepted a boat that was transporting a box with several pairs
of shoes in which 10 kilograms of cocaine and two kilograms of
heroin had been hidden.
</P>
<P>
Anti-drug police regional director Colonel Luis Carlos Ortiz
told the press that two men were detained in the boat with the
package, and added that the boat planned to dock in several
Caribbean ports.
</P>
<P>
Two kilograms of cocaine were also found in a mail pouch in
Bogota's Eldorado international airport.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Jose Aristides Puentes, anti-drug police chief in
Eldorado international airport, said the package contained six
pairs of shoes with two kilograms of cocaine hidden in the soles.
</P>
