<HEADLINE> Indonesia Names Best Athletes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- I. Gusti Made Oka Sulaksana and
Supriati Sutono were named 1998's best men's and women's athletes
of Indonesia at the Sports Awards ceremony held at the TVRI (
Indonesian Central Television) on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Oka and Supriati won gold medals from yachting and track and
field respectively to give two of six gold medals by the
Indonesian sporting delegation in last year's Asian Games in
Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The nomination list of the men's athletes category also
included Bangkok gold medalists -- Arif Taufan Samsudin in karate
and Ricky Subagja/Rexy Mainaky in badminton. However, Oka's
achievement was considered to be phenomenal, given that Indonesia
had never won in the Asian arena.
</P>
<P>
Supriati cruised to national sports' top honor, thanks to her
remarkable performance in the track and field arena in Bangkok
where she upset the likes of tough runners from Japan and China.
On the night of the Awards, Supriati beat Elyza/Deyana Lomban (
badminton), Yayuk Basuki (tennis), Omita Olga Ompi and Sandra
Aryani, both from karate.
</P>
<P>
Supriati's Bangkok victory seemed to pave the way for her coach
Nicky Pattiasina to win the Best Coach Award.
</P>
<P>
The Best Team Award went to the national badminton team, which
snatched the Thomas Cup -- the supreme trophy in the world's men's
team competitions -- in Hong Kong last year.
</P>
<P>
Badminton also took honors in the other categories with wins by
Subagyo Hadisiwoyo and Taufik Hidayat.
</P>
<P>
Subagyo, a four-star general Army chief, was named the Best
Sporting Patron, while Taufik the Best Hopeful.
</P>
<P>
The Awards presentation was co-organized by sports journalists,
the country's sports governing body KONI, Sports Ministry and
state-run TVRI.
</P>
<P>
The organizers also made awards to a number of national
sporting identities who dedicated their lives to sports in this
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
