<HEADLINE> Floods in Colombia Kill 3, 30 Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A landslide caused by
the flooding of the San Jorge River in the mountain area in
Colombia's Cordoba department has led to the death of three
persons, while 30 are reportedly still missing.
</P>
<P>
Two bridges and a number of houses have also been reported
damaged or destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Authorities said on Friday that intense rainfall in the Nudo
del Paramallo region caused the water in the San Jorge River to
spill over its banks and destroy houses, crops, and two bridges.
</P>
<P>
Cordoba department's control and rescue agencies declared the
area under a red alert. Authorities said the water volume upriver
could increase again and affect houses further downstream.
</P>
</TEXT>
