<HEADLINE> Peony 380-Years-Old Discovered in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A 380-year-old peony has been
discovered in a villager's home in the city of Chifeng in north
China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The peony is 1.5 meters high, and its crown exceeds two meters
in diameter.
</P>
<P>
The plant is believed to have been brought by a bride of noble
origin in Beijing to the villager's ancestor, and a study of the
flower shows it is of a fine peony variety that originated in
China.
</P>
<P>
Gardeners in Inner Mongolia discovered the peony by accident
while gathering plants for the upcoming '99 International
Horticulture Exposition which will be held in Kunming, capital of
southwest China's Yunnan Province, from May 1 to October 31 this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
