<HEADLINE> Russian FM, Albright to Hold Talks on Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov and U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright will meet in
Oslo, the capital of Norway, next Tuesday to discuss the crisis in
Kosovo, the Russian Foreign Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is aimed at jointly seeking a political solution to
the Kosovo crisis. The two officials are also expected to discuss
current relations between Russia and the United States, the ITAR-
Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
This is the first formal meeting between Ivanov and Albright
since NATO launched air strikes against Yugoslavia on March 24.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chairman of the State Duma (Russia's lower house of
parliament) Gennady Seleznyov said Russian President Boris Yeltsin
supported Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic's request for his
country's membership in the Russia-Belarus union.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov said if it joins the union, Yugoslavia would get
military technology aid from Russia while Russian troops and
fleets could be deployed in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Unlike Belarus, Yugoslavia shares no border with Russia.
</P>
