<HEADLINE> Man United Fans Hail Government Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Manchester United fans hailed the
Government's decision to block BSkyB's 623 million pounds bid to
buy the club as a "victory for football on Friday".
</P>
<P>
Secretary of State for Trade and Industry, Stephen Byers, ruled
against the takeover following an investigation into the deal by
the Monopolies and Mergers Commission.
</P>
<P>
The Independent Manchester United Supporters Association (IMUSA)
, which has been in the vanguard of the fight to stop the takeover,
claimed Byers' decision was not just a victory for them, but the
whole game.
</P>
<P>
IMUSA chairman Andy Walsh said: "The announcement today is not
just a tremendous victory for the fans of Manchester United, but a
victory for football.
</P>
<P>
"Back at the beginning of September when the takeover was made
public, nobody gave us a snowball's chance in hell of blocking the
bid.
</P>
<P>
"But, through a passionate belief in the need for Manchester
United to remain independent, we have succeeded.
</P>
<P>
"That is due to the overwhelming opposition of the majority of
Manchester United fans.
</P>
<P>
"United fans from all over the world have contacted us to voice
their opposition and offer their support.
</P>
<P>
"But we could not have done this on our own and we have had
support from fans all over the country, from Slough Town to
Newcastle United, and that is why this is a victory for football.
</P>
<P>
"Our feeling is one of absolute euphoria," he said.
</P>
<P>
Former United manager, Tommy Docherty, added his name to the
list of relieved supporters, saying: "I'm absolutely delighted and
the fans will be too.
</P>
<P>
"A football club belongs to football supporters -- not to
companies.
</P>
<P>
"Fans around the world will be celebrating, not only in
Manchester, but in Zambia, Tokyo and Germany.
</P>
<P>
"And they'll all be thrilled to bits I'm sure. My main concern
was that BSkyB would run football -- and they're not football
people,"he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
