<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Foreign Investment on Energy, Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China welcomes investment on
its energy and environment projects from American enterprises,
visiting Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. enterprises in this field are welcomed to continue their
active participation in the construction of energy and environment
projects in China, Zhu said in a speech at a roundtable session
attended by heads of over 10 famous U.S. energy and environment
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that with the further implementation of the
sustainable development strategy of China, its energy and
environment industries such as electricity, petroleum and gas,
environment protection are facing an unprecedented opportunity for
development, creating more favorable conditions for the China-U.S.
cooperation in this field.
</P>
<P>
The roundtable meeting was also attended by U.S. Vice President
Al Gore, who co-chaired with Premier Zhu the second session of the
China-U.S. Forum on Environment and Development.
</P>
<P>
The two countries Friday signed two documents of intention on
energy and environment cooperation and the Protocol to the
Agreement between China and the United States Relating to Civil
Air Transport.
</P>
<P>
China and the United States have strengthened bilateral
cooperation in energy and environment protection in recent years.
</P>
<P>
In March 1997, China and the U.S. established the forum on
environment and development. U.S. Vice President AL Gore attended
the first session of the China-U.S. Forum on Energy and
Environment in Beijing in 1997.
</P>
<P>
"They consider it a critical challenge to develop and
effitiently use energy resources, protect the global environment,
and promote environmentally sound growth and development," said a
China-U.S. Joint Statement issued in October 1997 following the
talks between Chinese President Jiang Zemin and U.S. President
Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
The principal areas of bilateral cooperation in this field
include clean energy, urban air pollution control, rural
electrification, and global environment issues such as climate
change, desertification and bio-diversity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
