<DOCNO> XIE19990410.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks End Mixed On Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Friday with Dow Jones industrial average falling while other
major indexes rising.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed down 23.86 at 10,173.84 as traders paused to
take profits from good performance on the blue chips this week
while keeping an eye on NATO strike against Yugoslavia. The
index set new records three times this week.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts believed that the Dow index was taking a
breather after a run to new highs. The index rose 365.19 points
in the past four days and nearly 11 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Good news on the economy drove other stock indexes
higher. The Labor Department reported that prices paid to
producers such as factories and refineries rose merely a 0.2
percent in March, suggesting inflation remain in check and the
Federal Reserve have no reason to raise interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index was up 19.66
at 2,593.05 while the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up
4.37 at 1,348.35.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 2.31 at 626.59 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 5.57 at 727.50. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 5.97 at 405.86.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,724 up, 1,292 down and 551
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume decreased to 707.24 million shares from 838.83
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
